<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symmetric_game" titl=
e=3D"Symmetric game">Symmetric game</a></div>
<p>A symmetric game is a game where each player earns the same payoff when =
making the same choice. In other words, the identity of the player does not=
 change the resulting game facing the other player.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-21" =
class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_theory#ci=
te_note-21"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-brac=
ket">]</span></a></sup> Many of the commonly studied 2=C3=972 games are sym=
metric. The standard representations of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Game_of_chicken" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Game of chicken">chic=
ken</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prisoner%27s_dilemma" tit=
le=3D"Prisoner's dilemma">the prisoner's dilemma</a>, and the <a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stag_hunt" title=3D"Stag hunt">stag hunt</a> ar=
e all symmetric games.
</p><p>The most commonly studied asymmetric games are games where there are=
 not identical strategy sets for both players. For instance, the <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultimatum_game" title=3D"Ultimatum game">ult=
imatum game</a> and similarly the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Dictator_game" title=3D"Dictator game">dictator game</a> have different str=
ategies for each player. It is possible, however, for a game to have identi=
cal strategies for both players, yet be asymmetric. For example, the game p=
ictured in this section's graphic is asymmetric despite having identical st=
rategy sets for both players.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Zero-sum_/_non-zero-sum"><s=
pan id=3D"Zero-sum_.2F_non-zero-sum"></span>Zero-sum / non-zero-sum</h3><sp=
an class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span>=
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DGame_theory&amp;act=
ion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D7" title=3D"Edit section: Zero-sum / non-zero-sum"=
><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span=
></div>
