<p>Some scholars see game theory not as a predictive tool for the behavior =
of human beings, but as a suggestion for how people ought to behave. Since =
a strategy, corresponding to a Nash equilibrium of a game constitutes one's=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Best_response" title=3D"Best resp=
onse">best response</a> to the actions of the other players =E2=80=93 provi=
ded they are in (the same) Nash equilibrium =E2=80=93 playing a strategy th=
at is part of a Nash equilibrium seems appropriate. This normative use of g=
ame theory has also come under criticism.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-78" class=3D"r=
eference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_theory#cite_note-78=
"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>76<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup>
</p><p><span class=3D"anchor" id=3D"Economics"></span>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Economics">Economics</h3><s=
